answers.body_markdown:
Looks like when you clicking `driver.navigate().back()` and then catching `StaleElementReferenceException` (that is for sure appeared in your case after order processing), your pages has not been rendered yet when you&#39;re calling `find_elements`.

Try to wait for at least one element to exist or visible in `catch` block and only then get list of elements.

```java
 } catch (StaleElementReferenceException staleException) {
   // Re-identify the order link after a StaleElementReferenceException
   WebDriverWait wdwait = new WebDriverWait(driver, 10);
   orderLinks = wdwait.until(ExpectedConditions.presenceOfAllElementsLocatedBy(By.xpath(&quot;//a[starts-with(@href, &#39;/dashboard/orders/&#39;)]&quot;)));
 } catch (Exception innerException) {
// your code 
}
                      
```

Also, more good appoach is not to catch stale element reference exception, but to loop through elements collection via element index and re-init orderLinks array after `driver.navigate().back();`

I guess your collection length after processing order would be still the same (so you can just go to the next element with index++)

Using this approach you shouldn&#39;t handle processed orders (index always would be incremented in next iteration), and your code would be a bit cleaner and shorter.

